<div id="pf271" class="pf w0 h0" data-page-no="271"><div class="pc pc271 w0 h0"><img class="bi x0 y8 w3 h5" alt="" src="bg271.png"/><div class="t m0 x9 h1b y2d7 ff1 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">35.4.4<span class="_ _b"> </span>Peripheral Additional Info register (USB<span class="ff7 ws24e">x</span>_ADDINFO)</div><div class="t m0 x9 hf ybf ff3 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Reads back the value of the fixed Interrupt Request Level (IRQNUM) along with the</div><div class="t m0 x9 hf y282 ff3 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Host Enable bit.</div><div class="t m0 x9 h7 y2a78 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Address: 4007_2000h base + Ch offset = 4007_200Ch</div><div class="t m0 x81 h1d y2a79 ff2 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws284">Bit<span class="_ _165"> </span>7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0</div><div class="t m0 x1 h7 y36fa ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws439">Read<span class="_ _1ff"> </span>IRQNUM<span class="_ _ec"> </span>0 IEHOST</div><div class="t m0 x8b h7 y36fb ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">Write</div><div class="t m0 x12c h7 y36fc ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws289">Reset <span class="ls1c4 ws28a v1b">00000001<span class="_ _19a"></span></span></div><div class="t m0 x16 h9 y36fd ff1 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws20b">USB<span class="ff7">x</span><span class="ws0">_ADDINFO field descriptions</span></div><div class="t m0 x12c h10 y36fe ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws259">Field Description</div><div class="t m0 x1 h7 y36ff ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">7–3</div><div class="t m0 x50 h7 y3700 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">IRQNUM</div><div class="t m0 x83 h7 y36ff ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Assigned Interrupt Request Number</div><div class="t m0 x1 h7 y3701 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">2–1</div><div class="t m0 x91 h7 y3702 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">Reserved</div><div class="t m0 x83 h7 y3701 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This field is reserved.</div><div class="t m0 x83 h7 y3702 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This read-only field is reserved and always has the value 0.</div><div class="t m0 x97 h7 y370d ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">0</div><div class="t m0 x60 h7 y370e ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">IEHOST</div><div class="t m0 x83 h7 y370d ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">When this bit is set, the USB peripheral is operating in host mode.</div><div class="t m0 x9 h1b y370f ff1 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">35.4.5<span class="_ _b"> </span>OTG Interrupt Status register (USB<span class="ff7 ws24e">x</span>_OTGISTAT)</div><div class="t m0 x9 hf y3710 ff3 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Records changes of the ID sense and VBUS signals. Software can read this register to</div><div class="t m0 x9 hf y3711 ff3 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">determine the event that triggers interrupt. Only bits that have changed since the last</div><div class="t m0 x9 hf y3712 ff3 fs5 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">software read are set. Writing a one to a bit clears the associated interrupt.</div><div class="t m0 x9 h7 y3713 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Address: 4007_2000h base + 10h offset = 4007_2010h</div><div class="t m0 x81 h1d y3714 ff2 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws284">Bit<span class="_ _165"> </span>7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0</div><div class="t m0 x1 h7 y2812 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">Read</div><div class="t m0 x45 h7 y3387 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws43a">IDCHG ONEMSEC</div><div class="t m0 xaf h7 y2812 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">LINE_</div><div class="t m0 x25 h7 y3387 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">STATE_</div><div class="t m0 x1e h7 y3388 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">CHG</div><div class="t m0 x132 h7 y2812 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls279">0<span class="ls0 v18">SESSVLDC</span></div><div class="t m0 x6c h7 y3715 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">HG</div><div class="t m0 x7d h7 y3716 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">B_SESS_</div><div class="t m0 x15a h7 y3715 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">CHG</div><div class="t m0 x98 h7 y2812 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">0</div><div class="t m0 x165 h7 y3387 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">AVBUSCHG</div><div class="t m0 x8b h7 y3717 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0">Write</div><div class="t m0 x12c h7 y161c ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws289">Reset <span class="ls1c4 ws28a v1b">00000000<span class="_ _19a"></span></span></div><div class="t m0 x30 h9 y3718 ff1 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws20b">USB<span class="ff7">x</span><span class="ws0">_OTGISTAT field descriptions</span></div><